---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - DearDates">
  <main class="w-full max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-8 pt-12 pb-24">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <a
        href="/"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-text-dim hover:text-white transition-colors mb-8"
      >
        <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-lg">arrow_back</span>
        <span class="font-mono text-sm uppercase">Back to Home</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <article class="max-w-none">
      <header class="mb-12 border-b border-surface-border pb-12">
        <h1
          class="text-6xl md:text-7xl font-black text-white tracking-tighter leading-[0.9] mb-4"
        >
          PRIVACY POLICY
        </h1>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2">
          Dear Dates
        </h2>
        <p class="text-text-dim font-mono text-sm uppercase">
          Last Updated: 2026-01-10
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class="mb-12 border-b border-surface-border pb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">INTRODUCTION</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Welcome to Dear Dates ("we," "our," or "the app").
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
          Your privacy is a core value of Dear Dates. This Privacy Policy
          explains how information is handled when you use our iOS application.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12 border-b border-surface-border pb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">
          OUR PRIVACY COMMITMENT
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Dear Dates is designed to work without collecting, tracking, or
          transmitting your personal data.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
          All information you enter stays on your device and remains fully under your
          control.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12 border-b border-surface-border pb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">
          INFORMATION WE STORE (LOCALLY ON YOUR DEVICE)
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Dear Dates stores all data locally on your iOS device only. We do not
          operate servers and do not sync or transmit your data.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Local Data Storage</h3>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The app may store the following information on your device:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-3 mb-6">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              <strong>Profile Information:</strong> names, photos, notes, and other
              details you choose to save
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              <strong>Event Information:</strong> birthdays, anniversaries, and custom
              events
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              <strong>Gift Information:</strong> gift ideas, notes, and history
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              <strong>User Profile:</strong> your own profile information, if you
              create one
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              <strong>App Settings:</strong> theme preferences, accent colors, and
              notification settings
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              <strong>Notification Data:</strong> minimal notification information (event names, dates, reminder days) stored separately for notification delivery
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              <strong>App Preferences:</strong> language settings, onboarding completion status, and other preferences stored using iOS UserDefaults
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          All data is stored using SwiftData, Apple's native data persistence
          framework, and UserDefaults for app preferences.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
          We do not access, transmit, back up, or sync this data to any external
          servers or cloud services.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12 border-b border-surface-border pb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">PHOTO LIBRARY ACCESS</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          If you choose to add photos to profiles, Dear Dates may request access
          to your Photo Library.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">This access:</p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-3 mb-4">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Is requested only when you tap "Add Photo"
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Is used solely to select photos for profiles inside the app
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Copies selected photos into the app's local storage
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Does not share photos with any external services
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
          You can revoke photo access at any time in iOS Settings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12 border-b border-surface-border pb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">NOTIFICATIONS</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Dear Dates uses local notifications to remind you of upcoming events.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          These notifications:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-3 mb-4">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Are scheduled and delivered entirely on your device
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Do not use servers or external services
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Do not transmit any personal data
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Can be disabled at any time in the app settings or iOS Settings
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Require minimal data (event names, dates, reminder days) to be stored separately for delivery when your device is locked
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Use iOS file protection mechanisms and are accessible only after your device is first unlocked following a restart
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12 border-b border-surface-border pb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">
          INFORMATION WE DO NOT COLLECT
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Dear Dates does not collect, transmit, or store:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed"
              >Analytics data</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed"
              >Usage statistics</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed"
              >Third-party analytics</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed"
              >Advertising identifiers</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed"
              >Device identifiers</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">Location data</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">Tracking data</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed"
              >Third-party tracking information</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Personally identifiable information outside your device
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mt-4">
          Dear Dates does not use third-party crash reporting services and does not collect crash data outside Apple's standard development and distribution tools.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12 border-b border-surface-border pb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">
          DATA STORAGE AND SECURITY
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Your data is stored locally on your device and protected by iOS
          security mechanisms.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">This means:</p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-3 mb-4">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Your data never leaves your device through Dear Dates
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Your main database is encrypted by iOS using NSFileProtectionComplete and is accessible only when your device is unlocked
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Notification-related data is stored separately using NSFileProtectionCompleteUntilFirstUserAuthentication to ensure reminders work correctly
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Your data may be included in encrypted device backups managed by
              Apple, depending on your iOS settings
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Dear Dates does not access, control, or manage these backups
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
          All file protection and encryption are handled by iOS and follow Apple's security best practices.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12 border-b border-surface-border pb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">
          DATA SHARING AND TRANSMISSION
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Dear Dates does not share, sell, rent, or transmit your data to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-3 mb-6">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed"
              >Third-party services</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed"
              >Advertising networks</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed"
              >Analytics providers</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed"
              >Cloud storage providers</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed"
              >External servers or databases</span
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
          The only way your data can leave your device is if you explicitly
          export it using the app's export feature.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12 border-b border-surface-border pb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">
          DATA EXPORT AND DELETION
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          You remain in full control of your data.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">You can:</p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-3 mb-4">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Export all your data at any time as a JSON file using the app's export feature
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Import previously exported data using the app's import feature
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Search and filter your data within the app (all processing is performed locally)
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Delete individual profiles, events, or gift ideas
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Remove all data by uninstalling the app
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Reset app preferences by uninstalling and reinstalling the app
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">THIRD-PARTY SERVICES</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Dear Dates does not use third-party services that collect or transmit
          personal data.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The app uses only Apple-provided frameworks, including:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-3 mb-4">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">SwiftUI</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">SwiftData</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed"
              >UserNotifications</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">Photos</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">Foundation</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">UserDefaults</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
          No advertising, analytics, crash reporting, or cloud synchronization
          services are used.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12 border-b border-surface-border pb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">CHILDREN'S PRIVACY</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Dear Dates is not specifically designed for children under the age of 13.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
          If you believe that a child has provided personal information within the app, please contact us so we can address the issue.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section class="mb-12 border-b border-surface-border pb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">
          CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
          Any changes will be reflected by updating the "Last Updated" date and
          making the revised policy available in the app or online.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12 border-b border-surface-border pb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">YOUR RIGHTS</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          You have the right to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed"
              >Access all data stored in the app</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed"
              >Export your data at any time</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed"
              >Delete your data at any time</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Control photo access via iOS Settings
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-primary text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
              Control notification permissions via app settings or iOS Settings
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12 border-b border-surface-border pb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">CONTACT</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you can contact
          us at:
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
          <a
            href="mailto:max.qb@icloud.com"
            class="text-primary hover:text-white transition-colors underline"
          >
            Email: max.qb@icloud.com
          </a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12 border-b border-surface-border pb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">INTERNATIONAL USERS</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          This Privacy Policy is intended to align with major privacy
          regulations, including GDPR, CCPA, and COPPA, to the extent
          applicable.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
          Because all data is stored locally on your device and not transmitted,
          Dear Dates provides a high level of privacy protection regardless of
          your location.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section class="mb-12 border-b border-surface-border pb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">CONCLUSION</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Dear Dates is built with privacy at its core.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-4">
          We don't collect your data.
          We don't track you.
          We don't share your information.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed">
          Your memories stay private — exactly where they belong: on your
          device.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
  /* Ensure custom classes work on privacy policy page */
  .text-text-dim {
    color: #888888 !important;
  }

  .border-surface-border {
    border-color: #262626 !important;
  }

  .bg-surface-dark {
    background-color: #141414 !important;
  }

  .bg-surface-border {
    background-color: #262626 !important;
  }

  .bg-background-dark {
    background-color: #0d0d0d !important;
  }

  .text-primary {
    color: #0d93f2 !important;
  }

  .bg-primary {
    background-color: #0d93f2 !important;
  }

  .border-primary {
    border-color: #0d93f2 !important;
  }
</style>
